# Agent Workflow

## Delivery pipeline (canonical)

Implementation delivery uses **OKF dispatch**, not background workers.

```bash
scripts/okf-dispatch init-pipeline --task-id TASK-0001
scripts/okf-dispatch consume --role builder
scripts/okf-dispatch complete --role builder --evidence runs/builder/...
scripts/okf-dispatch consume --role tester
# ... reviewer, integrator
```

See `docs/okf-dispatch-orchestration.md` and `.okf/workflows/multi-agent-delivery-pipeline.md`.

## Lifecycle planning (Forge)

Forge MCP servers produce stage plans and signed packets. Promote reviewed artifacts to OKF per `.okf/workflows/okf-forge-lifecycle-bridge.md`.

## Backlog (optional human tracker)

`backlog/queue.yaml` and `backlog/tasks/TASK-*.md` remain for human planning. Agents should trace work to OKF concepts via `okf_concepts` in task frontmatter when used.

## Handoff

When pausing or transferring work, write `.okf/handoffs/YYYY-MM-DD-task.md` using the handoff template. Inputs and outputs may also follow `schemas/handoff.schema.json`.

## Rules

- Read `.okf/index.md`, `.okf/project.md`, relevant concepts, and recent handoffs before substantive changes.
- Do not store secrets in OKF.
- Forge advisory outputs do not auto-promote to `verification_status: accepted`.
- Human integrator review required for OKF promotion and merge decisions.
